Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
check_ldb_version(25.10)                              check_ldb_version(25.10)

Name
       check_ldb_version  -  Reports  the LDB version, size, and the source of
       the software that is used to generate the library database (LDB) file

Syntax
         check_ldb_version

       -ldb<string>

       [-help]

       Reports the LDB version, size, and the source of the software  that  is
       used  to  generate  the library database (LDB) file. The LDB is Cadence
       binary library format.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -ldb<string>
              Specifies the LDB (library database) file whose version is to be
              printed.

Examples
       The following example displays the missing features/recommendations for
       the library database cell_w.db:

       > check_ldb_version -ldb cell_w.ldb

       The output is as shown below:

       LDB file compiled with tool version: v15.20 ((64bit)  mm/dd/yyyy  08:40
       (Linux 2.6.18-371.el5))

       File Size is xxxxx

       Source Tool: Innovus

